21 3–905.
22 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION, “MAIL” MEANS AN ITEM THAT HAS BEEN OR IS
23 INTENDED TO BE DELIVERED BY USE OF THE U.S. POSTAL SERVICE OR A COMMON
24 CARRIER OR DELIVERY SERVICE TO A PERSON WHOSE ADDRESS APPEARS ON THE
25 ITEM.
26 (2) “MAIL” INCLUDES AN ADDRESSED LETTER, A POSTAL CARD, OR A
27 PACKAGE.
28 (B) A PERSON MAY NOT KNOWINGLY AND INTENTIONALLY OPEN MAIL
29 ADDRESSED TO ANOTHER WITHOUT THE PERMISSION OF THE OTHER OR THE
30 OTHER’S AUTHORIZED REPRESENTATIVE OR DESIGNEE.

6 SENATE BILL 410
1 (C) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS GUILTY OF A MISDEMEANOR
2 AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT EXCEEDING 1 MONTH OR
3 A FINE OF $1,000 OR BOTH.
4 3–905.1.
5 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
6 INDICATED.
7 (2) “ARROW KEY” MEANS A KEY DESIGNED EXCLUSIVELY FOR
8 ALLOWING AN EMPLOYEE OF THE U.S. POSTAL SERVICE OR A COMMON CARRIER OR
9 DELIVERY SERVICE TO ACCESS A MAILBOX OR OTHER DEPOSITORY FOR STORING
10 MAIL.
11 (3) “MAIL” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 3–905 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
12 (B) (1) A PERSON MAY NOT COMMIT THEFT UNDER § 7–104 OF THIS
13 ARTICLE INVOLVING AT LEAST 1 BUT FEWER THAN 16 ITEMS OF MAIL.
14 (2) A PERSON MAY NOT COMMIT THEFT UNDER § 7–104 OF THIS
15 ARTICLE INVOLVING 16 OR MORE ITEMS OF MAIL.
16 (3) A PERSON MAY NOT COMMIT THEFT UNDER § 7–104 OF THIS
17 ARTICLE INVOLVING ONE OR MORE ITEMS OF MAIL USING AN ARROW KEY.
18 (C) A PERSON MAY NOT POSSESS AN ARROW KEY WITH THE INTENT TO USE
19 OR ALLOW THE USE OF THE ARROW KEY IN THE COMMISSION OF A VIOLATION OF
20 THIS SECTION.
21 (D) (1) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES SUBSECTION (B)(1) OF THIS SECTION IS
22 GUILTY OF A MISDEMEANOR AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT
23 NOT EXCEEDING 6 MONTHS OR A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $1,000 OR BOTH.
24 (2) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES SUBSECTION (B)(2) OF THIS SECTION IS
25 GUILTY OF A FELONY AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT
26 EXCEEDING 2 YEARS OR A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $2,000 OR BOTH.
27 (3) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES SUBSECTION (B)(3) OF THIS SECTION IS
28 GUILTY OF A FELONY AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT
29 EXCEEDING 5 YEARS OR A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $5,000 OR BOTH.
30 (4) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION IS
31 GUILTY OF A FELONY AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT
